The game Cumi is played by two players on a noshape board with nobasis tiling. Player one plays with Jaguars. Player two plays with Dogs. Rules for Pieces: Dogs step adjacent. Jaguars hop adjacent or step adjacent. Players take turns moving. Setup: Place a Dog for player two at the union of the bottom sites of the board expanded by 1 steps and the vertexes with coordinates [A3, E3]. Place a Jaguar for player one on site C7.. Rules: Move one of your pieces. Aim: If there are no pieces owned by Player the next player, the next player loses If the moving player is Draw, it's a draw. The Cumi (Ludii 1) ruleset.
